ZCZC GE95
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE MARITIME AND COASTGUARD AGENCY
AT 022300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE WILL LIE ACROSS THE N SEA WITH
A COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE DEVELOPING TO THE W OF THE BRITISH ISLES.
BY MIDDAY MONDAY A DOMINANT LOW 997 IS EXP TO FORM S OF IRELAND WITH THE
RIDGE DECLINING. THE LOW WILL THEN TRACK ACROSS SERN UK WHILE DPN DURING
MONDAY NIGHT BEFORE REACHING THE SERN N SEA AROUND 990 ON TUESDAY. THE LOW
WILL THEN TRACK NE AND SLWY FILL DURING WEDNESDAY. THIS WILL ALLOW A TRANSIENT
RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE TO FORM OVER THE UK AHEAD OF ANOTHER DEVELOPING ATLANTIC
SYSTEM. STRG WINDS EXP TO DEVELOP S OF 55 N LATER ON MONDAY. DURING TUESDAY
STRG WINDS WILL SPREAD TO ALL PARTS WITH A RISK OF GALES ESPECIALLY LATER
S OF 54 N. THERE IS A CONTINUED RISK OF GALES ACROSS THE SERN N SEA ON WEDNESDAY
BEFORE WINDS START TO EASE LATER
